{
  "texts": [
    "Biased samples are problematic for two reasons.",
    "First, transparency.",
    "Access to the input data for AI polls provides only partial, and certainly insufficient, information on the AI pollsters' methodology.",
    "Spotting a bias in the inputdata does not necessarily mean there will be a bias in the same direction in the output (the predictions), depending on the specific modeling choices of the pollster.",
    "Without fully understanding the models, we are unable to hold the pollster accountable."
  ]
}